context: In the United States, two of the wealthiest nonprofit organizations are the <a0_0><b5_0>Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation<b5_0/><a0_0/>, which has an endowment of <a2_0>US$38 billion<a2_0/>, and the <a1_0><b6_0>Howard Hughes Medical Institute<b6_0/><a1_0/> originally funded by <b9_0>Hughes Aircraft<b9_0/> prior to divestiture, which has an endowment of approximately <a3_0><b8_0>$14.8 billion<b8_0/><a3_0/>. Outside the United States, another large NPO is the <a4_0>British Wellcome Trust<a4_0/>, which is <b7_0>a "charity"<b7_0/> by British usage. See: List of wealthiest foundations. Note that this assessment excludes universities, at least a few of which have assets in the tens of billions of dollars. For example; List of U.S. colleges and universities by endowment.
